OL,3,CDangerous cyclists could face tougher
OL,4,Cprison sentences under new proposals
OL,6,FThe Victorian law introduced in 1861
OL,7,Fmeans cyclists aren't subject to the
OL,8,Fsame rules as car drivers, because the
OL,9,Fcurrent law only appplies to
OL,10,F"mechanically propelled" vehicles.
OL,12,FMotorists can face a life sentence if
OL,13,Fthey're convicted of causing death by
OL,14,Fdangerous or reckless driving.
