OL,3,CDangerous cyclists could face tougher
OL,4,Cprison sentences under new proposals
OL,6,F"These amendments would see the
OL,7,Fcreation of an "offence of causing
OL,8,Fdeath or serious injury by dangerous,
OL,9,Fcareless or inconsiderate cycling", as
OL,10,Fwell as an offence of killing someone
OL,11,Fthrough "inconsiderate" cycling. The
OL,12,Famendments would also require a bike
OL,13,Fto be "equipped and maintained" to
OL,14,Fstandards set out in the Act."
OL,16,FUnder the current rules, the maximum
OL,17,Ftwo-year sentence for "wanton and
OL,18,Ffurious driving" by a cyclist is
OL,19,Freduced by a third if the defendant
OL,20,Fpleads guilty.
