OL,4,Cprison sentences under new proposals
OL,6,FThe changes put forward by Sir Iain
OL,7,Fare also backed by a number of senior
OL,8,FConservatives, including Suella
OL,9,FBraverman, Sir Robert Buckland, and
OL,10,FSir Jacob Rees-Mogg.
OL,12,FA Westminster source told the
OL,13,FTelegraph newspaper: "There is general
OL,14,Facceptance around the House of Commons
OL,15,Fthat this should be done: the only
OL,16,Fquestion is how it should be done."
OL,18,FSpeaking to the newspaper, motoring
OL,19,Flawyer Nick Freeman, who is nicknamed
OL,20,F"Mr Loophole", has urgently called for
OL,21,Fthe amendments to become law.
